Catch non-finite rdpe mantissa in mpf_set_rdpe; signal failure to caller.

Background:
  On 2026-05-25/26, PSMM brute-force scans at N=470 and N=478 (10-scan
  production batch on scan-box) crashed deterministically with SIGFPE
  ~30-90 minutes in, mid-NNZ=3 enumeration. A gdb session caught the
  fault: the signal is *raised by GMP itself* via __gmp_invalid_operation,
  called from __gmpf_set_d when handed a NaN or Inf double.

  Backtrace at SIGFPE (faulting thread):

    #4  __gmp_invalid_operation        (libgmp.so.10)
    #5  __gmpf_set_d                   (libgmp.so.10)
    #6  mpf_set_rdpe                   (libmps/floating-point/link.c:23)
    #7  mps_msrad                      (libmps/unisolve/solve.c:218)
    #8  mps_mrestart                   (libmps/common/starting.c:1673)
    #9  mps_msolve                     (libmps/unisolve/solve.c:955)
    #10 mps_mahler_mpsolve_implementation
    #11 estimate_mahler_reciprocal_polynomial_d   (mahlerestimator.h:51)
    #12 PSMM worker lambda             (psmm.cpp:323)

  mps_msrad computes a cluster's scaled radius by iterating over the
  cluster's roots and reading each root's `drad` (an rdpe_t). For
  certain high-degree polynomials in PSMM's search space, one of these
  rdpe values has a non-finite mantissa (Inf or NaN) -- some upstream
  arithmetic in mpsolve overflowed without re-normalising the rdpe.
  Once the corrupted rdpe reaches mpf_set_rdpe, GMP aborts the process.

What this patch does:
  In mpf_set_rdpe, check isfinite(mantissa) before passing to mpf_set_d.
  On non-finite input:

    1. SET A THREAD-LOCAL FAILURE FLAG (mps_advanpix_computation_failed)
       so the caller can detect that this mpsolve invocation produced
       potentially-corrupted output.

    2. EMIT A DETAILED DIAGNOSTIC including the offending polynomial's
       degree and half-coefficients (read from caller-registered
       thread-local context: mps_advanpix_current_poly_*), plus the
       thread id, the bad mantissa, and its exponent. The diagnostic
       is built in a stack buffer and emitted with a single fputs call
       to avoid multi-thread interleaving.

    3. SET THE DESTINATION mpf TO 0 and return. This prevents the
       immediate SIGFPE but does NOT pretend the result is valid --
       the failure flag tells the caller to discard.

  Pavel 2026-05-26: "We cannot allow incorrect Mahler measure
  computation during search, that is unacceptable. We can skip and
  report the polynomial, but we cannot pass it as normal." This patch
  is the mpsolve half of that contract; the PSMM half is to clear the
  flag before each mps_*_mpsolve call, check it after, and if set
  treat the polynomial as "uncomputable -- skip + log for offline
  investigation" rather than use the (now invalid) Mahler measure.

  The thread-local diagnostic-context registration interface (set in
  mahlerestimator.h / rootfinder.h before each mpsolve call) provides
  the polynomial info that the diagnostic prints. Without registration
  the diagnostic still fires but says "(no caller-side context
  registered)".

  This is a *containment + signalling* fix. The longer-term work is
  to chase the upstream cause -- which mpsolve arithmetic produces
  the non-finite rdpe -- using the diagnostic-captured polynomial as
  a minimal reproducer, and either fix it in mpsolve_ext or report
  upstream to the mpsolve maintainers.

Symbols exported by this patch (all weak / thread-local):

  __thread const int *  mps_advanpix_current_poly_half;
  __thread int           mps_advanpix_current_poly_n;
  __thread const char *  mps_advanpix_current_poly_tag;
  __thread int           mps_advanpix_computation_failed;

  Callers should set the first three before each mps_*_mpsolve call
  (so the diagnostic can identify the polynomial) and read the fourth
  after each call (to detect failure). Tests / library consumers that
  don't care can ignore them -- the defaults give correct behaviour
  (no diagnostic context, no failure detection).

Verified-on: PSMM 2026-05-26 build; mpsolve 3.2.2 with patches 0001+0002.

--- a/src/libmps/floating-point/link.c	2026-05-26 07:45:46.639093403 +0900
+++ b/src/libmps/floating-point/link.c	2026-05-26 08:22:35.530049155 +0900
@@ -12,6 +12,79 @@
 
 
 #include <mps/link.h>
+#include <math.h>
+#include <stdio.h>
+#include <pthread.h>
+
+/*
+ * Advanpix diagnostic + failure-signalling hook. Callers register the
+ * polynomial being processed in thread-local storage; the defensive
+ * guard in mpf_set_rdpe (below) sets a failure flag and prints the
+ * offending polynomial when a non-finite rdpe mantissa is detected.
+ * See patch 0003 header for full background.
+ *
+ * Registration fields (caller sets before each mps_*_mpsolve call):
+ *   mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs       -- pointer to coefficient array
+ *   mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs_size  -- number of ints in the array
+ *   mps_advanpix_current_poly_n            -- polynomial degree (informational)
+ *   mps_advanpix_current_poly_tag          -- short label naming the call site
+ * Failure flag (caller reads after each call):
+ *   mps_advanpix_computation_failed
+ * Per-polynomial diag-emit counter (caller MUST reset to 0 before each call):
+ *   mps_advanpix_diag_count
+ */
+__thread const int *  mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs       = (const int*)0;
+__thread int          mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs_size  = 0;
+__thread int          mps_advanpix_current_poly_n            = 0;
+__thread const char * mps_advanpix_current_poly_tag          = (const char*)0;
+__thread int          mps_advanpix_computation_failed        = 0;
+__thread unsigned long mps_advanpix_diag_count               = 0;
+
+/* Cap stderr diagnostic emissions to MAX events PER POLYNOMIAL (the
+ * counter is reset by the caller before each mps_*_mpsolve call).
+ * This way each unique offending polynomial gets a bounded amount of
+ * detailed mpsolve-state info even if the bad rdpe is re-read many
+ * times during the same mpsolve iteration. The failure flag itself
+ * is set on every occurrence regardless of the rate limit, so the
+ * caller always knows the result is invalid. */
+#define MPS_ADVANPIX_DIAG_MAX 5
+
+static void
+mps_advanpix_emit_non_finite_rdpe (double m, long exp_e)
+{
+  /* Build the diagnostic in one stack buffer so concurrent writes
+   * from other threads don't interleave inside a single line. Worst
+   * case poly: N=1000 -> 1001 coeffs * 6 chars = 6006 bytes; round up. */
+  char buf[16384];
+  int  off = 0;
+  off += snprintf (buf + off, sizeof (buf) - off,
+                   "[mpsolve] mpf_set_rdpe: non-finite mantissa "
+                   "m=%.17e exp=%ld thread=%lu\n",
+                   m, exp_e, (unsigned long) pthread_self ());
+  const int * c     = mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs;
+  int         sz    = mps_advanpix_current_poly_coeffs_size;
+  int         N     = mps_advanpix_current_poly_n;
+  const char *tag   = mps_advanpix_current_poly_tag;
+  if (c && sz > 0)
+    {
+      off += snprintf (buf + off, sizeof (buf) - off,
+                       "[mpsolve] offending polynomial: tag=%s N=%d "
+                       "coeffs(size=%d) =",
+                       tag ? tag : "(none)", N, sz);
+      for (int i = 0; i < sz && off < (int) sizeof (buf) - 16; i++)
+        off += snprintf (buf + off, sizeof (buf) - off,
+                         " %d", c[i]);
+      off += snprintf (buf + off, sizeof (buf) - off, "\n");
+    }
+  else
+    {
+      off += snprintf (buf + off, sizeof (buf) - off,
+                       "[mpsolve] offending polynomial: "
+                       "(no caller-side context registered)\n");
+    }
+  fputs (buf, stderr);
+  fflush (stderr);
+}
 
 /***********************************************************
 **              link functions                            **
@@ -20,7 +93,21 @@
 void
 mpf_set_rdpe (mpf_t f, rdpe_t e)
 {
-  mpf_set_d (f, rdpe_Mnt (e));
+  double m = rdpe_Mnt (e);
+  if (!isfinite (m))
+    {
+      /* GMP's mpf_set_d would raise SIGFPE on non-finite input.
+         Set the failure flag so caller discards, emit a diagnostic
+         (rate-limited per polynomial), zero the destination to keep
+         mpsolve from crashing, and return. */
+      mps_advanpix_computation_failed = 1;
+      if (mps_advanpix_diag_count < MPS_ADVANPIX_DIAG_MAX)
+        mps_advanpix_emit_non_finite_rdpe (m, (long) rdpe_Esp (e));
+      mps_advanpix_diag_count++;
+      mpf_set_ui (f, 0);
+      return;
+    }
+  mpf_set_d (f, m);
   if (rdpe_Esp (e) >= 0)
     mpf_mul_2exp (f, f, rdpe_Esp (e));
   else
